WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.000
Good morning, Jacob. Happy Monday. Here is your week in

00:00:04.000 --> 00:00:08.000
review for the week of April thirteen through nineteen, two

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:12.000
thousand and twenty-six. Welcome to the weekly edition — the

00:00:12.000 --> 00:00:16.000
Sunday newspaper to your daily briefing's Twitter feed. We slow

00:00:16.000 --> 00:00:20.000
down. We zoom out. We find the patterns you might

00:00:20.000 --> 00:00:24.000
have missed when each day was happening to you at

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:28.000
full speed. Grab your coffee. Let's see what kind of

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:32.000
week that actually was. If you had to write a

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:36.000
one-sentence headline for the week of April thirteenth, it would

00:00:36.000 --> 00:00:40.000
be this: the week everything accelerated all at once. You

00:00:40.000 --> 00:00:44.000
started Monday with the Anthropic application freshly submitted — confirmation

00:00:44.000 --> 00:00:48.000
email at one thirteen A-M — and a U-S naval

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
blockade of Iranian ports beginning at ten A-M Eastern. That

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:56.000
is a lot of world for one Monday. By Friday,

00:00:56.000 --> 00:01:00.000
the company you had just applied to was sitting down

00:01:00.000 --> 00:01:04.000
with the White House chief of staff. By Saturday, Iran

00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:08.000
had reinstated its closure of the Strait of Hormuz. And

00:01:08.000 --> 00:01:12.000
somewhere in the middle of all of this, you went

00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:16.000
to a book festival, had dinner with your parents at

00:01:16.000 --> 00:01:20.000
the Top Ten, watched the S-and-P five hundred cross seven

00:01:20.000 --> 00:01:24.000
thousand for the first time, and got a text from

00:01:24.000 --> 00:01:28.000
Katelyn on Saturday night that had very little to do

00:01:28.000 --> 00:01:32.000
with geopolitics. The week had a shape to it. It

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:36.000
moved from anticipation — the application, the blockade, all those

00:01:36.000 --> 00:01:40.000
open questions — through a brief, dazzling optimism on Thursday

00:01:40.000 --> 00:01:44.000
when markets celebrated a possible ceasefire extension, and then back

00:01:44.000 --> 00:01:48.000
into tension by Sunday as Iran reinstituted the blockade and

00:01:48.000 --> 00:01:52.000
the April twenty-second expiration clock started ticking louder. On the

00:01:52.000 --> 00:01:56.000
personal axis, the trajectory went the other direction: from the

00:01:56.000 --> 00:02:00.000
anxiety of the job posting getting pulled to a quieter,

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:04.000
more important kind of clarity that arrived Saturday night from

00:02:04.000 --> 00:02:08.000
Tacoma. That is the week. Let's go deeper. Let's start

00:02:08.000 --> 00:02:12.000
with what went right, because there was more of it

00:02:12.000 --> 00:02:16.000
than the geopolitical noise suggests. First: the Anthropic application. It

00:02:16.000 --> 00:02:20.000
is worth saying clearly — you applied to one of

00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:24.000
the most consequential companies in the world, for a role

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:28.000
at the intersection of A-I safety and public policy, and

00:02:28.000 --> 00:02:32.000
you did it well. Katelyn's verdict was "you sound impressive."

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.000
That is the right standard. The outcome is not in

00:02:36.000 --> 00:02:40.000
your hands. The work was. Second: arXiv. The seven-day trial

00:02:40.000 --> 00:02:44.000
ran, the security papers earned their keep, and you made

00:02:44.000 --> 00:02:48.000
the call — permanent fixture. The decision is clean. The

00:02:48.000 --> 00:02:52.000
cluster of papers on agent security, prompt injection, and memory

00:02:52.000 --> 00:02:56.000
extraction formed a genuine policy reading list for the A-I

00:02:56.000 --> 00:03:00.000
governance doc you haven't started yet but are clearly going

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:04.000
to. Third: Unbound. You went to a book festival in

00:03:04.000 --> 00:03:08.000
Columbia with your parents while the rest of the internet

00:03:08.000 --> 00:03:12.000
was catastrophizing about the Strait of Hormuz. Your dad flagged

00:03:12.000 --> 00:03:16.000
the A-I panel. You stayed at Mom and Dad's Friday

00:03:16.000 --> 00:03:20.000
night. You had a Top Ten dinner. That is a

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:24.000
win no prediction market is tracking. Fourth: Project Arete, week

00:03:24.000 --> 00:03:28.000
one. The daily briefing infrastructure got real this week —

00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:32.000
feedback loops, market tracker, arXiv permanence, concept note candidates. The

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:36.000
briefing itself became a better product in real time. Production

00:03:36.000 --> 00:03:40.000
over consumption, the hike insight from Monday, is already showing

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:44.000
up in the outputs. And finally: Katelyn's friend Kyley is

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:48.000
having a baby girl in September. That is not your

00:03:48.000 --> 00:03:52.000
win, exactly, but it felt like one anyway. Two stories

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:56.000
ran all week and changed shape every day. Let's track

00:03:56.000 --> 00:04:00.000
them. Iran and the Strait of Hormuz. Monday started with

00:04:00.000 --> 00:04:04.000
the blockade announcement and oil at one hundred and three

00:04:04.000 --> 00:04:08.000
dollars a barrel. Day one felt like the beginning of

00:04:08.000 --> 00:04:12.000
something serious. Day two, the same — allies refusing to

00:04:12.000 --> 00:04:16.000
join, the blockade settling in, European markets shrugging. Then something

00:04:16.000 --> 00:04:20.000
unexpected happened. Thursday morning, Pakistani mediators entered Tehran, both sides

00:04:20.000 --> 00:04:24.000
signaled interest in extending the ceasefire past its April twenty-second

00:04:24.000 --> 00:04:28.000
deadline, and Trump told reporters the war was "close to

00:04:28.000 --> 00:04:32.000
over." The S-and-P five hundred crossed seven thousand for the

00:04:32.000 --> 00:04:36.000
first time in history. Markets believed him. Oil eased back

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:40.000
under one hundred dollars. By Friday it felt like, maybe,

00:04:40.000 --> 00:04:44.000
the blockade had worked as a negotiating tactic. That optimism

00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:48.000
lasted about forty-eight hours. Saturday, Iran reclosed the strait. The

00:04:48.000 --> 00:04:52.000
ceasefire window is closing Tuesday. And this morning, Sunday into

00:04:52.000 --> 00:04:56.000
Monday, the U-S Navy had seized an Iranian vessel, no

00:04:56.000 --> 00:05:00.000
tankers at all are transiting the strait, and the C-N-B-C

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
headline reads "resumption of hostilities." The Polymarket odds on Hormuz

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:08.000
normalization by April thirtieth, which had climbed to twenty-four percent

00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:12.000
on Friday's peace signal, are about to get repriced. The

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.000
honest read: the blockade has not produced a deal. It

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:20.000
has produced a deadline. That deadline is Tuesday, April twenty-second.

00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:24.000
Everything this week points toward Pakistan as the venue for

00:05:24.000 --> 00:05:28.000
another round of talks. Whether those talks happen before the

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:32.000
ceasefire formally expires — and what happens if they don't

00:05:32.000 --> 00:05:36.000
— is the story to watch first thing this week.

00:05:36.000 --> 00:05:40.000
Europe has approximately six weeks of jet fuel reserves. That

00:05:40.000 --> 00:05:44.000
is not an abstraction. The Anthropic story had four distinct

00:05:44.000 --> 00:05:48.000
acts this week, and they are worth tracking in sequence.

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:52.000
Act one: Monday through Wednesday — the good news avalanche.

00:05:52.000 --> 00:05:56.000
Bloomberg reported investor offers at eight hundred billion dollars —

00:05:56.000 --> 00:06:00.000
more than double the February round. Anthropic's annualized revenue is

00:06:00.000 --> 00:06:04.000
at thirty billion dollars. The Information reported Opus four point

00:06:04.000 --> 00:06:08.000
seven could drop as early as that week. The Treasury

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:12.000
Department was urgently seeking Mythos access. OpenAI's investors were reportedly

00:06:12.000 --> 00:06:16.000
getting nervous about their own valuation. On Wednesday, it felt

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
like the company you had applied to was ascending in

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
real time. Act two: Thursday through Friday — the launch

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:28.000
and the backlash. Opus four point seven appeared on Google

00:06:28.000 --> 00:06:32.000
Vertex Thursday, officially launched Friday, and the Reddit verdict was

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:36.000
brutal. "Serious regression." Terminal-Bench was down from four point six.

00:06:36.000 --> 00:06:40.000
The community that had been celebrating Anthropic's rise turned on

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
the launch almost immediately. Meanwhile, Claude Design launched Thursday and

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
Figma lost seven percent of its market value in a

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:52.000
day. Anthropic shipped its first vertical product aimed at replacing

00:06:52.000 --> 00:06:56.000
an entire S-a-a-S category and barely paused to celebrate. Act

00:06:56.000 --> 00:07:00.000
three: Friday morning — the White House meeting. Dario Amodei

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:04.000
walked into the West Wing and sat down with Susie

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:08.000
Wiles and Scott Bessent to discuss the Mythos standoff. The

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:12.000
Pentagon wants unrestricted access. Anthropic has been saying no. The

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:16.000
meeting was characterized afterward as "productive and constructive." Trump, asked

00:07:16.000 --> 00:07:20.000
about it by reporters, said he had "no idea" Amodei

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:24.000
was there. Whether that is plausible deniability or genuine confusion

00:07:24.000 --> 00:07:28.000
about his own administration's schedule is left as an exercise

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:32.000
for the reader. Act four: Friday afternoon — the posting

00:07:32.000 --> 00:07:36.000
gets pulled. The Strategy and Operations, Public Policy and Public

00:07:36.000 --> 00:07:40.000
Benefit role was removed from Greenhouse on April sixteenth. You

00:07:40.000 --> 00:07:44.000
told Katelyn: "No interview offer for yours truly." That is

00:07:44.000 --> 00:07:48.000
the accurate, honest response. It also is not the whole

00:07:48.000 --> 00:07:52.000
story. The public policy team at Anthropic was, in the

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:56.000
same week, negotiating with the White House over the most

00:07:56.000 --> 00:08:00.000
contested A-I access question of the year. Hiring freezes during

00:08:00.000 --> 00:08:04.000
crisis weeks are normal. And here is the headline from

00:08:04.000 --> 00:08:08.000
Axios on April nineteenth that the Sunday briefing may have

00:08:08.000 --> 00:08:12.000
caught: the N-S-A is using Mythos Preview — actively, right

00:08:12.000 --> 00:08:16.000
now — despite the D-O-D's own supply chain risk label

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
on the company. The White House is reportedly working with

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:24.000
the O-M-B to route other federal agencies around the Pentagon's

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:28.000
blockade. The intragovernmental fight over Anthropic is bigger than any

00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:32.000
single job posting. Silence from Greenhouse is not a verdict.

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:36.000
The team is doing something consequential. Keep watching. The vault

00:08:36.000 --> 00:08:40.000
had a busy week. The daily briefings infrastructure got its

00:08:40.000 --> 00:08:44.000
biggest upgrade yet — prediction market tracker went live, concept

00:08:44.000 --> 00:08:48.000
note candidates file started accumulating, the arXiv trial produced its

00:08:48.000 --> 00:08:52.000
permanent verdict. The briefings themselves became more self-aware: Sunday's edition

00:08:52.000 --> 00:08:56.000
flagged its own tool failures in real time and ran

00:08:56.000 --> 00:09:00.000
a three-claim verification pass with no errors found. Career files

00:09:00.000 --> 00:09:04.000
saw the most action. Anthropic postings snapshots from April fifteenth,

00:09:04.000 --> 00:09:08.000
sixteenth, eighteenth, and nineteenth are all logged — a daily

00:09:08.000 --> 00:09:12.000
changelog of what the company is hiring for, in case

00:09:12.000 --> 00:09:16.000
the door reopens. The Sarah Heck outreach thread in Career-slash-Anthropic

00:09:16.000 --> 00:09:20.000
got its own file. The job updates April note is

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:24.000
being maintained. A research journal draft appeared: "Mirror Life" dated

00:09:24.000 --> 00:09:28.000
April fifteenth, filed under two thousand twenty-six. Worth knowing that

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:32.000
exists. The Binder Park Ramblings voice memo from Monday's hike

00:09:32.000 --> 00:09:36.000
got transcribed and filed. That document is the week's most

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:40.000
important vault entry, not because of what happened externally, but

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:44.000
because of what you figured out on a trail in

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:48.000
mid-Missouri: the A-I obsession is fine, the consumption-production imbalance is

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:52.000
the problem. Everything the week produced — the arXiv commitment,

00:09:52.000 --> 00:09:56.000
the daily briefing improvements, the policy doc you haven't started

00:09:56.000 --> 00:10:00.000
yet — follows from that one walk. Dustin's ReDefine Politics

00:10:00.000 --> 00:10:04.000
late-night development session ended up in the Social Life update.

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:08.000
The friendship where both of you are building things is

00:10:08.000 --> 00:10:12.000
the most alive thread in the social file right now.

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:16.000
Katelyn. The week began with the package landing — "Perfect,

00:10:16.000 --> 00:10:20.000
love it and you" — and ended with a Saturday

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:24.000
night text that deserves more than a Quick Hit. At

00:10:24.000 --> 00:10:28.000
approximately nine P-M Central, after a migraine day and a

00:10:28.000 --> 00:10:32.000
quiet afternoon trading tree photos, she sent: "I'm missing you

00:10:32.000 --> 00:10:36.000
a lot today. Really dreaming of us living together." The

00:10:36.000 --> 00:10:40.000
word "dreaming" is doing a lot of work. It is

00:10:40.000 --> 00:10:44.000
not "we need to have a conversation." It is not

00:10:44.000 --> 00:10:48.000
"I can't do this long distance anymore." It is the

00:10:48.000 --> 00:10:52.000
language of someone trying on an idea to see if

00:10:52.000 --> 00:10:56.000
it fits — sitting upstream of a demand, upstream of

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:00.000
an ultimatum, at the place where a person says something

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:04.000
true out loud for the first time to see how

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:08.000
it lands. The Anthropic posting got pulled the same week.

00:11:08.000 --> 00:11:12.000
The geography question is not more or less urgent because

00:11:12.000 --> 00:11:16.000
of that — but it is less abstract. Missouri-or-Washington used

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:20.000
to be a theoretical question. It is becoming a real

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:24.000
one. The July twenty-third through thirtieth Washington trip is ninety-five

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:28.000
days out. Flights are still unbooked. That trip was always

00:11:28.000 --> 00:11:32.000
more than a vacation. Now it is carrying the weight

00:11:32.000 --> 00:11:36.000
of the conversation that will either start or not start

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:40.000
in person. Family had a warm quiet week. Ben is

00:11:40.000 --> 00:11:44.000
in New York with family. Alex Kelley is sending iPhone

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:48.000
eighteen Pro color rumors on a reliable schedule. Dustin is

00:11:48.000 --> 00:11:52.000
building his politics app on Windows and just cancelled his

00:11:52.000 --> 00:11:56.000
ChatGPT subscription in favor of Claude. The social perimeter is

00:11:56.000 --> 00:12:00.000
holding. Here is what the calendar looks like. The biggest

00:12:00.000 --> 00:12:04.000
event of the week has nothing to do with your

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:08.000
personal schedule: the Iran ceasefire expires Tuesday, April twenty-second. Pakistan

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:12.000
talks are reportedly still possible. If they happen before Tuesday,

00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:16.000
watch oil and the S-and-P. If they don't, watch oil

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:20.000
and the S-and-P. Capital City Race is May ninth —

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:24.000
that is nineteen days from today. Molly's Miles is off

00:12:24.000 --> 00:12:28.000
the board. The training window for Capital City is now

00:12:28.000 --> 00:12:32.000
and it is not long. Washington trip is July twenty-third

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:36.000
through thirtieth. At some point this week, look at flights

00:12:36.000 --> 00:12:40.000
from K-C or St. Louis to Seattle. They were expensive

00:12:40.000 --> 00:12:44.000
last week; prices fluctuate. WWDC is June eighth — fifty

00:12:44.000 --> 00:12:48.000
days out. The foldable iPhone prediction market is at eighty-five

00:12:48.000 --> 00:12:52.000
percent. Alex is already tracking every color rumor for the

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:56.000
eighteen Pro. This is going to be a loud spring.

00:12:56.000 --> 00:13:00.000
On the Anthropic front: no action needed. The process is

00:13:00.000 --> 00:13:04.000
running. If there is going to be a screen, the

00:13:04.000 --> 00:13:08.000
window is roughly April twentieth through the twenty-fifth. If nothing

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:12.000
comes in that window, the posting was pulled before your

00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:16.000
application surfaced in a review — which means the question

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:20.000
is whether it reopens. Check the postings scanner. The A-I

00:13:20.000 --> 00:13:24.000
policy doc is the week two production target. The Binder

00:13:24.000 --> 00:13:28.000
Park hike said so. The arXiv papers keep forming arguments

00:13:28.000 --> 00:13:32.000
for it. The policy landscape — N-S-A using Mythos against

00:13:32.000 --> 00:13:36.000
D-O-D wishes, OpenAI's cyber model, the Stanford A-I Index —

00:13:36.000 --> 00:13:40.000
is giving you everything you need to start. Three things

00:13:40.000 --> 00:13:44.000
worth tracking as the week unfolds. First: the Iran ceasefire

00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:48.000
expiration on Tuesday. The range of outcomes is wide. Full

00:13:48.000 --> 00:13:52.000
extension with Pakistan talks resuming is possible. A formal lapse

00:13:52.000 --> 00:13:56.000
that turns into de facto continuation is possible. An escalation

00:13:56.000 --> 00:14:00.000
that makes last Monday's oil spike look like a warmup

00:14:00.000 --> 00:14:04.000
is possible. Europe's six-week jet fuel clock is the most

00:14:04.000 --> 00:14:08.000
concrete number in the story. Second: the intragovernmental Anthropic fight.

00:14:08.000 --> 00:14:12.000
The N-S-A is using Mythos. The D-O-D says Anthropic is

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:16.000
a supply chain risk. The O-M-B is building workarounds. The

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:20.000
White House meeting was "productive." What actually happens with government

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:24.000
access to Anthropic's frontier models will define how the next

00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:28.000
generation of A-I policy gets made — and it is

00:14:28.000 --> 00:14:32.000
happening this week. Third: what you produce. The first week

00:14:32.000 --> 00:14:36.000
of Project Arete built infrastructure. The second week is supposed

00:14:36.000 --> 00:14:40.000
to produce something. The A-I policy doc is the obvious

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:44.000
candidate. Nineteen days to Capital City means training matters too.

00:14:44.000 --> 00:14:48.000
The question for week two: what gets built? That is

00:14:48.000 --> 00:14:52.000
your week, Jacob. The naval blockade, the book festival, the

00:14:52.000 --> 00:14:56.000
White House meeting, the posting that got pulled, the S-and-P

00:14:56.000 --> 00:15:00.000
crossing seven thousand, the Figma shareholder who definitely had a

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:04.000
bad Thursday, and a Saturday night text from Tacoma that

00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:08.000
said something true. The week of April thirteenth was not

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:12.000
an easy one by conventional measures. But it had shape.

00:15:12.000 --> 00:15:16.000
It moved. And underneath all the volatility — the oil

00:15:16.000 --> 00:15:20.000
prices and the prediction markets and the Greenhouse silence —

00:15:20.000 --> 00:15:24.000
there was the quieter story of someone figuring out what

00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:28.000
he actually wants to build, and a person two thousand

00:15:28.000 --> 00:15:32.000
miles away who is dreaming about the same future. April

00:15:32.000 --> 00:15:36.000
twenty-second is Tuesday. The ceasefire clock is ticking. But some

00:15:36.000 --> 00:15:40.000
deadlines are more important than others. Go run. Start the

00:15:40.000 --> 00:15:43.200
doc. Check the flights. Have a good week.
